Already at breakfast, butter and tea containing milk alone contain more than ten of the possibly carcinogenic residues and three of the safely proven carcinogenic residues, as well as more than twenty residues that can affect the hormone system.
The apple imported from Brazil, intended as a snack for the study, has traces of six chemical substances, including a fungicide banned in France.
The same applies to the green beans from Kenya, included in lunch, where the study found traces of a strictly banned insecticide in the EU.
In addition, the hacksteak, the tuna from the can, even the baguette and the chewing gum of pesticides and other chemical substances were sprinkled.
In tap water, the analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
At dinner, the salmon steak was "richest" with 34 chemical residues detected, and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not unloaded.
The final risk of this "pollutant cocktail" for the consumer is "probably undervalued", according to the study.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie-Les Verts (EE-LV) has in turn proposed "in view of the urgency of the situation" to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop the "increase in diseases of civilization".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) identified 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables that are consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
